# 📡 Radio Spot Watcher DX — v9.0

> Now badged **NEURAL DX WATCHER v9.0** in the interface.

**DX Cluster Dashboard & Advanced Radio Analysis Engine**

A local web application for DX monitoring and radio analysis, designed for the demanding amateur radio operator.  
Built to **observe**, **understand** and **step back** — not to generate visual noise.

---

## 🧭 Overview

**Radio Spot Watcher DX** is a local web application that:

- connects to one or more **DX Clusters (Telnet)**
- displays **real-time spots** (HF / VHF / UHF)
- integrates **solar indices** (SFI, A, Kp…)
- maintains a **usable memory** of activity
- offers **multiple reading levels**, from live monitoring to strategic analysis

> The goal is not to see a lot,  
> but to **see clearly**.

---

## 🖥️ Main Pages

### 1️⃣ **Index** Page — Real-time & Operator Tracking

Immediate observation page.

Displays:
- live spot stream
- active bands
- wanted DX (*wanted*)
- solar indices
- **activity surge** alerts

👉 **Goal: know what's happening right now.**

---

### 📡 **WATCHLIST · Tracking** Panel

A feature introduced to answer a simple need:

> *"I wasn't at my desk — what did I miss?"*

- based on the watchlist
- uses an in-memory history
- shows the latest spots per callsign

Philosophy:
- ❌ not a raw log
- ❌ not a massive data dump
- ✅ a catch-up tool
- ✅ designed for the human operator

---

### 2️⃣ **Map** Page — Observation Map (micro-view)

Classic map of **individual spots**:

- each point = **one station**
- immediate geographical representation
- instant snapshot

👉 **Goal: see where it's happening.**

The **Map** page is an **execution tool**.

---

### 3️⃣ **Analysis** Page — Deferred META ANALYSIS

A deliberately **non-real-time** tool, based on application log analysis.

👉 **A tool for stepping back**, not a gimmick.

---

### 4️⃣ **World** Page — Forecast & Anomalies

The **World** page is **fundamentally different** from the Map page.

| Page | Nature | Question |
|---|---|---|
| Map | Raw observation | Who is active right now? |
| World | Interpreted analysis | Where is propagation abnormally favorable? |

- displays **zones**, not stations
- spatio-temporal clustering
- noise filtering
- controlled refresh rate

👉 **World decides, Map executes.**

### 5️⃣ **Briefing**

Updated every 12 hours, summarizing essential DX information. Offers the ability to automatically add callsigns to the **Watchlist** on the Index page. You won't miss any expedition — as soon as a callsign is spotted, it will be highlighted in yellow in the DX spots panel.

---

