## 🚀 Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/f1smv/spot-watcher-dx.git
cd spot-watcher-dx
chmod +x start.sh
./start.sh
```

The application will be available at `http://localhost:8000`

---

## ⚙️ Technical Architecture

- Backend: Python / Flask
- Frontend: HTML / CSS / JavaScript
- Cluster: Telnet DX Cluster
- Analysis: dedicated Python scripts
- Storage: memory + local JSON files

No cloud dependency.

---

## 🗂️ Version History

### v9.0 — NEURAL DX & COCKPIT 6 m mode

**Rebranding**

- The application becomes **NEURAL DX WATCHER v9.0** (page title and header)

**New mode selector (3 modes in the header)**

The 🧠 toggle is replaced by three exclusive buttons:

- ⚡ **CLASSIC** — classic layout (former BASIC mode)
- 🧠 **SMART** — intelligent analysis / scored Top Spots (former SMART mode)
- 🎛 **COCKPIT 6 m** — new full-screen dashboard dedicated to the 6 m band

The active mode is persisted in localStorage.

**COCKPIT 6 m mode — full rewrite**

A dense, dark "radio cockpit" interface (cyan/orange neon), laid out in 3 columns, hiding the classic dashboard. Panels:

- 📌 **6 m SUMMARY / 24H** — 24h spots, unique DXCC, SFI, K-index
- ☀️ **SOLAR & GEOMAGNETIC DATA** — SFI, A-index, K-index
- 📊 **BAND CONDITIONS · HF** — band status
- ⚡ **MAGIC BAND 6 m · DX ACTIVITY HEATMAP** — full-frame "broadcast" panel:
  - **E-Layer Hotspots** world map (Leaflet) with animated scan and HIGH/LOW legend
  - circular **Opening Strength** gauge (CLOSED → OPEN, 0–100 %)
  - **E-Layer Hotspots** list by zone (Europe, East Coast NA, Japan, Australia)
  - animated 🔴 **OPEN** badge when an opening is detected
- 📡 **HF PROPAGATION · VOACAP** — forecast with zone selector (EU / NA / AS / OC)
- 🧠 **INTELLIGENT 6 m TOP SPOTS** — dedicated scored 6 m selection
- **DX SPOT FEED · 6 m · 20 MIN** — feed of the latest 6 m spots
- 🎯 **DXCC OPPORTUNITIES** — LoTW cross-check
- 📡 **MANUAL SPOT** — direct send to the cluster

**Misc**

- Refined 6 m detection and visual harmonization with the rest of the app
- Cockpit layout patches (responsive ≤ 1250 px, VOACAP readability)

### v8.2 — LoTW persistence + 6m Magic Band panel + fixes

**LoTW — persistence across restarts**

- LoTW cache saved to `data/lotw_cache.json` after each sync
- Automatic reload at startup — no need to re-sync manually
- DXCC opportunities available immediately after a restart
- Deduplication fixed: same callsign (with or without /P /MM suffix) no longer appears multiple times

**⚡ DX 6M · MAGIC BAND panel** (SMART mode only)

- Dedicated 6m band panel, visible only in Smart mode
- Leaflet mini-map 320px with color-coded markers by distance (green >8,000 km, yellow >3,000 km)
- Table of top 25 spots, sorted by descending distance
- Animated 🔴 OPEN badge when 5+ active spots detected (automatic opening detection)
- Watchlist and beacon indicators on each spot
- Drag & drop enabled

**6m mode detection improved**

- 50.313 MHz → FT8 (instead of SSB)
- 50.318 MHz → FT4 (instead of SSB)

**Various fixes**

- DXCC Opportunities panel aligned with 4-column CSS grid
- Missing bands displayed on a dedicated line (↳ missing: ...)
- 6m table font and colors harmonized with DX WANTED panel

### v8.1 — Smart Mode improvements + World redesign

**TOP SPOTS panel — improvements**

- Drag & drop enabled on the Smart Mode panel
- Bilingual badge legend (FR/EN) displayed below the panel title
- New **Rarity** column with 4 levels:
  - 🔴 **MOST WANTED** — New DXCC + distance > 10,000 km
  - 🟡 **WANTED** — Watchlist or missing DXCC + distance > 8,000 km
  - 🔵 **TRACKING** — Call in watchlist
  - ⚡ **EXOTIC DX** — Distance > 10,000 km not in watchlist (animated orange badge)

**World page full redesign**

- Full-screen map — no more fixed sidebar
- Floating semi-transparent HUD with backdrop-filter
- Live stats: total zones / confirmed / suspect
- Greyline integrated directly in World
- Tooltips on propagation circles (band, spots, UTC time)
- Topbar consistent with the rest of the application
- Collapsible "How to read" section

### v8.0 — Smart Mode 🧠

**BASIC / SMART toggle in the header**

- 🧠 slider in the header — switches between BASIC mode (standard display) and SMART mode (intelligent analysis)
- Dedicated visual theme: background `#070B1A`, surfaces `#10172A`, cyan accent `#22D3EE` and violet `#8B5CF6`
- State persisted in localStorage — mode is remembered between sessions

**"TOP SPOTS · SMART MODE" panel**

In SMART mode, the HF table is replaced by a selection of the **15 best spots** ranked by composite score:

- 🔴 **+40 pts** — New DXCC never worked (LoTW cross-reference)
- 🟣 **+30 pts** — Call in the watchlist
- 🟢 **+10 pts** — Confirmed LoTW DXCC, missing band
- 🔵 **+20 pts** — Favorable propagation (SFI > 70)
- ⚡ **+30 pts** — Native SPD score (spot reliability)
- 📡 **+15 pts** — Distance > 10,000 km (long-range DX)

Each spot displays: callsign, colored badges, frequency / band / mode / time / distance, visual score bar.

